# nbstripout discipline (per `.pre-commit-config.yaml` nbstripout hook):
#
# Default: nbstripout strips output cells from .ipynb at commit time.
#
# v1.0.7 exception: `notebooks/*.ipynb` are committed WITH outputs frozen
# per /exploring-options batch 9 Q2 lock ("pre-rendered + frozen output
# cells"). These notebooks are reviewer-display artifacts rendered by
# Quarto + visible on the live site; they are executed once locally
# during v1.0.7 commit prep + committed with outputs intact. CI does
# NOT re-execute them. This is the disclosed Option-2 strategy in the
# v1.0.7 CHANGELOG; see ADR-053 + ADR-054 reading-guide governance.
notebooks/*.ipynb -nbstripout
